article.headline: St. Francis, NY 74, Fairleigh Dickinson 70
article.story: EDS: St. Francis, N.Y. 74, Fairleigh Dickinson 70. NEW YORK (AP) -- Robert Hines scored 23 points, including the tie-breaking free throw with 28 seconds left, to lead St. Francis, N.Y. to a 74-70 victory over Fairleigh Dickinson on Saturday. Hines broke a 70-70 tie with the first of two free throws. Ricky Cadell grabbed the offensive rebound and was fouled. He made one free throw and then capped the scoring with a layup at the buzzer after a steal. Jamaal Womack had 15 points and Cadell added 13 for the Terriers (7-21 4-13 Northeast Conference). Sean Baptiste had 25 points and Bernell Murray added 16 for the Knights (7-19, 3-13), who lost their fourth straight.
